val inputfile = sqlContext.read
							.format("com.databricks.spark.csv")
							.option("header", "true") // Use first line of all files as header
							.option("inferSchema", "true") // Automatically infer data types
							.option("delimiter", "\t")
							.load("/data/sidana/purch/diversity/data").withColumn("utcdate",unix_timestamp($"utcdate","yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss").cast("timestamp")).withColumnRenamed("cast(unixtimestamp(utcdate,yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss) as timestamp)","utcdate")

val clicks = inputfile.filter("wasClicked")
val distinctUserWeek = clicks.select($"userId",weekofyear($"utcDate")).distinct
val minWeek = distinctUserWeek.select(min(distinctUserWeek("weekofyear(utcdate)"))).head().getInt(0)
val maxWeek = distinctUserWeek.select(max(distinctUserWeek("weekofyear(utcdate)"))).head().getInt(0)
val start = minWeek+1
import org.apache.spark.sql._
      for(a<-start to maxWeek){
          val previous = a-1
          val dfPrevious = distinctUserWeek.filter(distinctUserWeek("weekofyear(utcdate)")===previous)
          val dfpresent = distinctUserWeek.filter(distinctUserWeek("weekofyear(utcdate)")===a)
          val previousUsers = dfPrevious.select("userId")
          val presentUsers = dfpresent.select("userId")
          val innerJoin = previousUsers.join(presentUsers,previousUsers("userId")===presentUsers("userId"))
          println(innerJoin.count)
      }

							.format("com.databricks.spark.csv")

val userClicks = inputfile.filter("wasClicked").groupBy("userId").count.withColumnRenamed("count", "numClicks")
